Introduction

IN A MINUTE is a South Korean boy group under JWIN Entertainment, whom debuted on March 15, 2025, with their first single album, UNBOXING: WHAT YOU WANTED. The trio—Juntae, Jaejun, and Hyunyeop—brings a wealth of experience, having previously been active in various groups and musical projects before coming together for this new endeavor.

Their journey began when MLD Entertainment announced on September 9, 2024, that the three members would hold a fan meeting under the name IN A MINUTE. The event, later confirmed for October 20, offered fans an early glimpse of the group's dynamic ahead of their official debut. On March 7, 2025, JWIN Entertainment officially confirmed their long-awaited debut date.

On April 4, 2025, IN A MINUTE officially announced their fandom name: INNING.
The name symbolizes the shared journey between IN A MINUTE and their fans, with each "inning" representing a meaningful moment spent together. Fans are encouraged to continue supporting the group unwaveringly through every step of their journey.
The group expressed gratitude for the continued love and support, asking fans to stay by their side—always, just like now.
